char bPARTblock::dosType[4]
 

0c0
Dos Type. "DOS" and the FFS/OFS flag only.

Also,
"UNI"\0 = AT&T SysV filesystem;
"UNI"\1 = UNIX boot filesystem;
"UNI"\2 = BSD filesystem for SysV;
"resv" = reserved (swap space).
